cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CL. 

The paper deals with distance metric learning in visual similarity search, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new loss function for learning image embeddings, which falls under the category of machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper evaluates its method on two datasets, Amazon fashion retrieval benchmark and DeepFashion in-shop retrieval data, which are related to multimedia and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also possible categories. Finally, the paper uses weakly labeled product description data to implicitly determine fine-grained semantic classes, which involves natural language processing. Hence, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a possible category.
